# Chocolate Sales Performance Report

**As of November 14, 2025**  
*Prepared for: Global Chocolate Division*  
*Data Period: January 2023 – September 2024*  

## Executive Summary
Our chocolate sales have demonstrated steady growth, achieving a total revenue of **$27.99 million** across 4,998 orders and 1,988,952 boxes sold. With 83% of orders delivered successfully, operations remain efficient. The UK and USA lead as key markets, while premium dark chocolate products drive the highest value. Recent months show stable performance at ~$1.25M per month, positioning us well for Q4 expansion. Focus on top performers and high-margin items could boost revenue by 10-15% in the coming quarter.

## Key Performance Metrics
| Metric                  | Value          |
|-------------------------|----------------|
| **Total Revenue**      | $27,990,857   |
| **Total Boxes Sold**   | 1,988,952     |
| **Total Orders**       | 4,998         |
| **Delivered Orders**   | 4,138 (83%)   |
| **Average Order Value**| $5,600        |

## Top Products by Revenue
Premium and organic lines dominate, accounting for ~35% of total sales.

| Rank | Product              | Revenue       |
|------|----------------------|---------------|
| 1    | Orange Choco        | $1,861,963   |
| 2    | Drinking Coco       | $1,850,362   |
| 3    | 99% Dark & Pure     | $1,845,754   |
| 4    | Organic Choco Syrup | $1,834,641   |
| 5    | Peanut Butter Cubes | $1,818,416   |

